(1)
Atlantic Avenue, east from 75th Street, seen from the avenue's north lane. Behind the wooden fence is the main line of the Long Island Railroad. In the left background is the wooden bridge over which runs Rockaway Boulevard.

P. L. Sperr
July 27, 1930

(2)
Atlantic Avenue, looking east from 78th Street and showing a closer view of the Rockaway Boulevard bridge.

P. L. Sperr
July 27, 1930
